1. Through the coordination role of the OPC, a joint Programme Steering Committee field visit with reflective session was organized in Mudzi/Mutoko from March 20-24th 2017 to better understand the role played by local community structures within the broader peace architecture. 
1.a Government through the OPC convened one Technical Committee Meeting (12th January), and four Programme Steering Committee Meetings (19th January, 5th April, 21st June and 19th July).
2.a	The NPRC Commissioners identified four pillars for capacity enhancement efforts in 2017. which were translated into learning programmes of capacity enhancement Retreats. Retreats were held on the concept of people affected by violent conflicts (5-9th June in Bulawayo), truth seeking and truth telling mechanisms (2-7th July in Harare), and post conflict justice, healing and reconciliation programmes (1-4 August in Kadoma).
2.b  A tailored NPRC Capacity Development plan was designed from February-March with input from regional experts. It was then delivered in the form of action oriented Retreats from May-August 2017. As a result, draft international frameworks and systems have been developed by the Commission and will feed into the Strategic Planning process scheduled for the 4th Quarter; 
2.c  The Commissioners have identified draft framework for internal tools and systems to be developed during the 4th Quarter;
2.d Draft Situational Analysis questionnaires were piloted through Church Based Organizations (ECLF and CCJP) in an effort to develop a comprehensive Early Warning mechanism;
